=== Sprint 2 · Task S2.1: Go ↔ Python strategy-service HTTP client ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §4.S2.1

--- Problem ---
V2 §2.D-3: Python backtest engine existed (strategy-service:8081) but was never called. PythonStrategyServer returned hardcoded mock data:
- Execute: {Success: true, Signal: {Reason: "mock execution"}}
- Backtest: {EquityCurve: [10000, 10050, 10100, 10080, 10150, 10200]} (6 hardcoded points)
- Validate: {Valid: true} (always true, no real validation)

--- Fix ---
Part 1 — internal/strategysvc/python_client.go (NEW):
- PythonClient struct: baseURL + http.Client (60s timeout)
- Backtest(BacktestRequest) → BacktestResult (equity_curve, sharpe_ratio, max_drawdown, etc.)
- Execute(ExecuteRequest) → ExecuteResult (signal with side/lots/price/sl/tp/reason)
- Validate(ValidateRequest) → ValidateResult (valid, errors, warnings)
- Health check: GET /api/health
- JSON marshaling with 400+ error handling

Part 2 — Rewrite python_strategy_handler.go:
- Added `client *strategysvc.PythonClient` field + SetClient() setter
- Execute: calls client.Execute() if available → maps to StrategySignal with correct field names (SignalType, Volume, Price, StopLoss, TakeProfit, Reason)
- Backtest: calls client.Backtest() → returns real equity_curve + BacktestMetrics (SharpeRatio, MaxDrawdown)
- Validate: calls client.Validate() → returns real Valid/Errors/Warnings
- All three fall back to mock data when client is nil or call fails (graceful degradation)

Part 3 — config and main.go wiring:
- Added StrategyServiceURL to Config struct + STRATEGY_SERVICE_URL env var
- main.go: if cfg.StrategyServiceURL != "", creates PythonClient and injects into PythonStrategyServer

